xxl.core.indexStructures

Class BPlusIndexedSet<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • xxl.core.indexStructures.IndexedSet<BPlusTree,E>
      • xxl.core.indexStructures.BPlusIndexedSet<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - The data type which should be managed
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<E>, Collection<E>, Set<E>, SortedSet<E>

    public class BPlusIndexedSet<E>
extends IndexedSet<BPlusTree,E>
    An implementation of the IndexedSet super class to use sets which are indexed by a BPlusTree.

      • BPlusIndexedSet

        public BPlusIndexedSet(BPlusTree tree,
                       BPlusTreeBuilder creator)
        Sets up a new instance of BPlusIndexedSet with an instance of BPlusTree and it's builder object. The builder instance contains different meta data for the index, e.g. the file path, the data type, containers and others.
        Parameters:
        tree - An instance of an BPlusTree
        creator - The BPlusTreeBuilder which created tree

      • sizeBigInteger

        public BigInteger sizeBigInteger()
        Description copied from class: IndexedSet
        Returns the size of the current set as BigInteger. Dependent on the underlying index structure the content amount is only limited by the hard drive capacity. It may comes to an overflow for standard Integer data which contains the set size. This methods guarantees the correct set size.
        Specified by:
        sizeBigInteger in class IndexedSet<BPlusTree,E>
        Returns:
        The set size
